/opt/scriptrunner/
├─ app.py               # Flask backend
├─ scriptrunner.db      # SQLite DB
├─ frontend/
│  └─ index.html        # Frontend HTML
├─ static/
│  └─ style.css         # Optional CSS
├─ uploads/             # For keyfiles
└─ .venv/   

Activate your virtualenv:

source .venv/bin/activate
pip install flask flask-cors paramiko

Start the app:
python3 app.py

Use tmux or screen (simpler, temporary)
run application in background:

cd /opt/scriptrunner
source .venv/bin/activate
nohup python3 app.py > flask.log 2>&1 &

1️⃣ Combine commands in a single SSH execution
Instead of sending multiple commands separately, combine them using && or ;:

[
  {"os":"ubuntu","cmd":"cd /opt/scriptrunner && ./installapache.sh"}
]


&& ensures the second command runs only if the first succeeds.
; will run the second command regardless of success of the first:

[
  {"os":"ubuntu","cmd":"cd /opt/scriptrunner; ./installapache.sh"}
]

2️⃣ Use full path

Instead of changing directories, just call the script with its full path:

[
  {"os":"ubuntu","cmd":"/opt/scriptrunner/installapache.sh"}
]



